        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 8:47PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 846 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Pendleton, moving north at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holdman, Pendleton, Rieth, Adams, Helix, Mission, and Umatilla
Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
